definitions.definition: A painful contraction of a muscle which cannot be controlled ; ( sometimes ) a similar pain even without noticeable contraction.
examples: He retired hurt at 31 due to a leg cramp .

definitions.definition: A clamp for carpentry or masonry .
A piece of wood having a curve corresponding to that of the upper part of the instep , on which the upper leather of a boot is stretched to give it the requisite shape.
